      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and 2% offset yield load are the primary quantities of interest for spinal implant mechanical performance assessment and directly map to the regulatory submission requirements for Class II pedicle screw systems."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for model risk 3.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the intended use scenario: quasi-static compression-bending of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct per ASTM F1717. The validation domain encompasses the loading regime, geometry, and material class of the intended application."
