    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level for model risk 3. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) reflects the single-condition F1717 protocol and is accepted given the regulatory standardisation of that test condition. Overall credibility is sufficient to support the intended use of the FEA model for compression-bending performance prediction of non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs.",
